
Overview of verb vaporise

The verb vaporise has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                     
1. evaporate, vaporise -- (cause to change into a vapor; "The chemist evaporated the water")
2. evaporate, vaporise -- (change into a vapor; "The water evaporated in front of our eyes")
3. gasify, vaporize, vaporise, aerify -- (turn into gas; "The substance gasified")
4. evaporate, vaporize, vaporise -- (lose or cause to lose liquid by vaporization leaving a more concentrated residue; "evaporate milk")
